    "created_at": "2015-07-07T23:11:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-07T23:11:27Z",
    "body": "Okay I've just tested it and yes you can build for all platforms locally with `electron-packager` - even though it is incredibly slow (and my laptop is a top spec core i7 with 16GB RAM) e.g. I did...\n\n```\nelectron-packager ./ {{appname}} --platform=all --arch=all --version=0.29.2 --out=./dist/\n```\n\nSo I still think some would prefer a build service hosted by Atom/GitHub themselves, especially those with less powerful laptops/PCs.\n"
