    "body": "@jasdeepkhalsa The first time yes, because it's downloading six bundles and packaging them up (since you used `all`). The second time it shouldn't be as slow, but even if it were, you're still packaging for six different platforms. Packaging my app for Windows, Linux, and Mac  (x64) only takes a min or two on my MBA 8 GB. I could however see the utility in such a service if you were building with native modules, because then you would have to compile on said platform.\n"
