    "updated_at": "2015-07-08T16:19:57Z",
    "body": "@jasdeepkhalsa I might have misunderstood, I thought you meant a service which takes care of building the finished binaries for all platforms? Normally this would need to include code-signing for Windows and Mac, as otherwise it won't run on those platforms or be caught by antivirus when downloaded by users. I guess you could have a third party service which does everything except code-signing, but then one would still need to automate the code-signing on Windows and Mac platforms. It might make more sense to have a local build process to do everything in one go.\n"
  },
